00:18:04.693 --> 00:18:09.120
You talk about genuine loving people, you talk about praying people.

00:18:09.120 --> 00:18:15.430
South Korea, those people pray and they are sincere.

00:18:15.430 --> 00:18:20.920
When you talk to those Asian brothers and sisters over there, they love the Lord.

00:18:20.920 --> 00:18:27.640
Not saying that we don't, but I am telling you there is a compassion and a passion that I have.

00:18:27.640 --> 00:18:41.552
Maybe it is because I am called to pray for the Asian brothers and sisters, especially North Korea, for the persecution that they receive from Kim.

00:19:07.440 --> 00:19:24.968
I truly believe with all my heart that God is going to remove that tyrant in the days ahead and that the people of North Korea will be liberated and have a window for a revival like we wouldn't believe.

00:19:34.640 --> 00:19:35.040
I still go back to the scripture that the Lord gave us: James 5:7.

00:19:52.880 --> 00:19:58.046
"Be patient, therefore, brethren, until the coming of the Lord.

00:19:58.046 --> 00:20:18.230
Behold, the husbandman waiteth for the precious fruit of the earth, and hath long patience for it, until he receives the early and the latter rain.

00:20:31.573 --> 00:20:31.938
" The early and the latter rain.

00:20:32.667 --> 00:20:34.360
I just lay hold to that scripture.

00:20:34.360 --> 00:20:39.640
People ask, "Bren, where is it at in the Bible about an end-time harvest?

00:20:39.640 --> 00:20:42.460
You keep talking about an end-time outpouring.

00:20:42.460 --> 00:20:49.303
" James 5:7 is enough right there to believe that we are going to see a lot of souls saved.

00:21:02.940 --> 00:21:03.250
Well, what about the great falling away?

00:21:04.799 --> 00:21:17.540
I am not trying to say there won't be because the Bible says there will be, but I know this: that God doesn't want any man to perish, but all to come to repentance.

00:21:21.097 --> 00:21:21.360
So I am just going to stand on James 5:7.

00:21:21.360 --> 00:21:25.279
"Be patient, therefore, brethren, until the coming of the Lord.

00:21:25.279 --> 00:21:36.103
Behold, the husbandman waiteth for the precious fruit of the earth, and hath long patience for it until he receives the early and the latter rain.

00:21:43.440 --> 00:21:43.680
" I just believe that God doesn't want any of us to perish.

00:21:43.680 --> 00:21:53.360
Just like 2 Peter 3:9, he doesn't want that any of us should perish, but all come to repentance.

00:21:53.360 --> 00:21:56.029
For God so loved the world.

00:21:59.000 --> 00:22:02.720
And I know that there's a lot of us that want to get out of here.

00:22:02.720 --> 00:22:17.554
But I really believe that God is coming after the one with the grannies and the grandpas and the grandmas and all the ones that are believing God for their unsaved loved ones to come into the saving knowledge of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:22:17.554 --> 00:22:26.707
I truly believe that God is doing one last call and we're about to see the greatest harvest of souls this world has ever seen.

00:22:26.707 --> 00:22:28.472
You say, Well, Brandon, when is it?

00:22:28.472 --> 00:22:33.640
I believe it's when we get busy doing it.

00:22:37.427 --> 00:22:43.269
We had 51 people just during the live stream last time give their heart to Jesus Christ and people emailing after said, Brandon, how many?

00:22:43.269 --> 00:22:49.829
Braden in the comments and everything you tell me there's so many people that are rededicating their life to Jesus.

00:22:49.829 --> 00:23:01.573
I bet, no exaggeration, we had well over 70 give their heart to Jesus Christ for the first time, some of them, and rededications on a little YouTube channel like this.

00:23:13.306 --> 00:23:13.520
People just clicking in and giving their heart to Jesus Christ.

00:23:20.360 --> 00:23:20.640
The harvest is plentiful and the laborers are few.

00:23:30.530 --> 00:23:30.820
I don't try to have petty differences with people.

00:23:35.150 --> 00:23:35.520
I truly don't.

00:23:38.320 --> 00:23:46.815
I stick to myself because I know how many people are dying and going to hell on a day-to-day basis and there are so many of them right now that don't know Jesus.

00:23:46.815 --> 00:23:55.679
When I saw the statistics that Braden had on there, as Diana brought it out of her old paper she had, she went to church growth.

00:23:55.679 --> 00:24:10.507
She had a class that she took there that was about church growth, how to plant and have church growth, how to make your church grow, how to basically evangelize better and things like that.

00:24:12.098 --> 00:24:18.072
And there was a statistic of how many people were leaving the body of Christ on a year-to-year basis.

00:24:23.600 --> 00:24:24.060
And the numbers were staggering.

00:24:29.279 --> 00:24:30.019
And that's why I'm trying to tell y'all what we got to come together.

00:24:30.019 --> 00:24:37.400
We got to come together and we have got to bring in this harvest with whatever we have.

00:24:37.400 --> 00:24:38.900
It's all hands on deck.

00:24:40.686 --> 00:24:41.029
You say, Well, I'm just a granny.

00:24:41.029 --> 00:24:42.663
I'm just a grandma.

00:24:42.663 --> 00:24:43.714
I'm over here.

00:24:43.714 --> 00:24:47.779
No, you're the prayer that's praying this thing back.

00:24:47.779 --> 00:24:58.137
Backing me in prayer, backing these people in prayer so that we can have some covering to get the job done.

00:24:59.200 --> 00:25:11.919
You wouldn't believe the spiritual bombardment we receive on a day-to-day basis that Diana and I and the children, we're so thankful for you grandmas and you people out there saying, Braden, I'm praying for you.

00:25:14.510 --> 00:25:21.538
I feel your prayers and I just want to say thank you for the persecution for the word's sake.

00:25:21.538 --> 00:25:30.439
I'm so thankful for all you that say, Hey, Braden, I'm praying for you.

00:25:30.439 --> 00:25:32.000
I'm praying for your wife.

00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:36.411
I'm praying for your marriage.

00:25:36.411 --> 00:25:38.578
I'm praying for you, Braden.

00:25:38.578 --> 00:25:41.486
I'm telling you, I'm a very uplifted person.

00:25:46.971 --> 00:25:47.817
I like to have fun.

00:25:52.310 --> 00:26:00.789
And if I come across sometimes to you all as a worrywart or sad or whatever, I am not.

00:26:00.799 --> 00:26:01.965
I like to enjoy life.

00:26:24.057 --> 00:26:24.343
I like to go and get ice cream with my kids and go sit down at the park and feed the ducks.

00:26:24.343 --> 00:26:29.760
I love to do things and do things with my special needs daughter.

00:26:29.760 --> 00:26:34.960
I like to see her smile whenever she's having a hard day.

00:26:34.960 --> 00:26:45.947
I like to, when she's crying or fussing and she's having a hard time, I love to see her.

00:26:45.947 --> 00:26:54.559
I can turn around by praying in the spirit and ask the Father, how do I make Megan's day better today?

00:26:54.559 --> 00:27:02.480
How do I bring a smile to that little girl's face?

00:27:10.133 --> 00:27:10.480
And sometimes it's just by a hug.

00:27:10.480 --> 00:27:20.380
Sometimes it's driving around in the car and you go get a tea with her, you know.

00:27:21.552 --> 00:27:21.848
I don't know.

00:27:23.031 --> 00:27:27.036
It just always seems like it's always been something that has been like a...

00:27:27.036 --> 00:27:38.080
because she doesn't, she's nonverbal, you know, and so you never know what she really wants.

00:27:38.080 --> 00:27:43.547
You have to guess whether it comes to food.

00:27:49.227 --> 00:27:49.573
I pray, what does Megan want to eat today?

00:27:49.573 --> 00:27:52.789
What would she like to have to eat?

00:27:52.789 --> 00:28:12.799
Because you know you have an opinion about what you eat and maybe you don't want to eat chili that day and so just because you know you feed it to her and she don't want to eat it, that's why I always try to, what would Megan want today?

00:28:12.799 --> 00:28:25.751
So I know the Holy Spirit knows, so I always ask him, can you tell me what Megan would want to eat today?

00:28:25.751 --> 00:28:27.280
She can't tell me.

00:28:27.280 --> 00:28:30.919
She, what would she like to drink today?

00:28:30.919 --> 00:28:32.489
She would she like a Coke?

00:28:32.489 --> 00:28:33.250
I don't know.

00:28:33.250 --> 00:28:39.252
I just think those are the times whenever you see those smiles because you heard it.

00:28:48.792 --> 00:28:52.049
You heard it when she smiles and she grins from ear to ear because she knew the Holy Spirit told me.

00:28:53.615 --> 00:28:53.807
I don't know.

00:28:53.807 --> 00:28:55.422
Those are just precious moments to me.

00:28:55.422 --> 00:29:04.204
It's the same thing when you just surprise your wife with a gift on Valentine's Day.

00:29:16.455 --> 00:29:16.863
She wasn't asking for nothing.

